As I said before, your logic is skewed ...considerably.  The 'conflict' of forming rotations is not within the powers of the RTA Admin to mediate as the judicial branch of our community.  Why?  Because there are no existing rules from which to base a fair and impartial decision on.  Without that, they are acting on sheer and simple opinion, what they PERCEIVE as being fair and impartial based on ...what?  Their experiences with the rotation mobs?  Their experiences with the people involved?  They simply can't do it ...and if they could ...what's the decision based on and how can it be proven to be the MOST FAIR MOST IMPARTIAL decision that could have been made?  &quot;Because I said so&quot;?<br>
<br>
Conflict requires exactly two things to exist ...1) two parties to be in contradiction with each other ...2) and some basis for the contradiction.  What kind of basis could their possibly be in the formation of a rotation?!?<br>
<br>
Party 1:  Dude, that mob spawns on a 24 hour timer.<br>
<br>
Party 2:  Dude, no it doesn't, it spawns on a 23 hour timer.<br>
<br>
