You are confused as to the difference between being a guild, and being a guild in the RTA, and being a guild in the RTA on a rotation.  <br>
<br>
Any guild may exist on the Rathe, and as long as they follow the rules as stated by SOE, noone can actively do anything against them.<br>
<br>
Any guild is a participant the RTA once they qualify for membership on either the calendars for the planes or have joined a rotation.  Being a participant means following the rules that the RTA has established from previous rotations about the mob, set of mobs, or zone.<br>
<br>
Once a guild has defeated a specific encounter, they then have the experience of dealing with it and may make informed commentary and decisions based on future ratifications/changes to a specific encounter ruling (rotation).<br>
