<b><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61993">Kalessin Shai`Tan</a> - <i>Dread Lord</i></b><br><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=599003">Porridge Oats</a> - <i>Animist</i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rigorre>Rigorre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Much ado about nothing</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/4/03 9:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Elemental planes forum</span><hr size=1> Seranis, I am impressed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You are confused as to the difference between being a guild, and being a guild in the RTA, and being a guild in the RTA on a rotation.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm not confusing any of these.  It's the sudden addition of another level entirely ...being in a guild in the RTA on an EP rotation ...that I have a problem with.  This isn't a simple matter of &quot;a guild in the RTA on a rotation&quot;...<br>
<br>
You act like what we have now with a private forum within the RTA, yet unaccountable to the RTA, is status quo around here.  It's not.  Sure, we have always had some separation among non-RTA guilds, RTA guilds, and RTA guilds on rotation, but never has that separation been so severe as to declare exclusion from the other entities making up the community.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rotations are formed for the purpose of sharing content. You agree with this, yet you argue that all should have input into how this content should be shared, despite the fact that the majority of the server has no clue what the content is like. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I have NEVER argued that the RTA Representatives should be allowed INPUT into the discussion of the forming of rotations in the EP forum.  My argument is concerned merely with the idea that the forum should be held accountable to the RTA Representatives for discussions NOT CONCERNING ROTATIONS ...non-rotation discussions that have been proven to exist ...while it is allowed to exist here in the RTA.<br>
<br>
By allowing the EP community to have their own little gated and controlled community within the RTA, the fairness and impartiality of the RTA is undermined.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Previously, you argued that you wanted the forum to be public without having an interest into having any input to how the rotations are established. Now you state that you do want input into the establishment of the rotation. So which is it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->When did I EVER say that &quot;I want input into the establishment of the rotation&quot;?  Name ONE TIME I've said that ...<br>
<br>
The closest I've ever come to saying such a thing is when I was talking about the technical capabilities of the EZBoard forum and the fact that Nyca says you can't have one group of individuals with read\post access and another group of individuals with only read access.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>It is technically not possible.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  But, &quot;technically not possible&quot; is not a reason to not give the RTA Reps access to that forum ...because it IS technically possible to give them read access ...you just have to give them post access as well ...and then you have to trust that they won't post to rotation matters that do not concern them, a rule I might add, all of them follow now in the RTA Rep forum.  <br>
<br>
Discussions take place about rotations all of the time in the Rep forum, and somehow these guys don't post comments to rotations discussions they are not on.  And, yet, in the EP forum they are all of a sudden going to lose control of themselves and just start randomly posting on issues they have no knowledge of?  They are going to take all of your uber secret information and post it to the General forum?  Puhhleeeze!  Who is being paranoid now?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There are far more shadow knights on the server than there are admins or elemental planes representatives. Additionaly, information posted in the SK forum will not include information that a guild would consider to be spoilers in the same manner that discussions about the EP encounters, for the purpose of establishing rotations, would. Your comparrison fails to note this.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->...and I once again ask you, what spoiler information can you possible give my guild, who isn't even IN the Elem Planes now, that you aren't going to give to us the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>very second</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> we kill RZtW?  It's idiocy to protect spoiler information from people who don't even meet the access requirement to the mobs and zones, those people who can put no useful purpose to that information  ...knowing damn well and good that you will freely give that SAME 'protected' spoiler information to those SAME people once they have gained access to the mobs and zones.  What kind of logic is that?<br>
<br>
It's just the EP guild community wanting to feel special ...wanting to bring your elite EP status here.  There is no other logical answer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You also attack the Admins over this matter, when it has been demonstrated time and time again that they will act counter to their own guild interests in trying to keep the game fair for all concerned.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->What they may or may not have done in the past has no bearing on this incident.  In THIS case, only one interest was represented in the decision to make a private forum ...the interest of the EP guild community ...of which 3 of the Admins belong.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Creating private forums is completely congruent to the RTA charter as long as the private forums created facilitate the discussion of rotations/agreements among guilds on The Rathe server &lt;period&gt; Any other believed pretense of these boards is simply ignorance on the part of the believer.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Private forums may or may not be 'congruent to the RTA charter' ...wherever this so-called charter might be located (someone might need to make one up real quick) ...but the fact remains that it wasn't in the powers of the RTA Admins to make that decision without RTA Rep authority.  You can sit there and claim assumed powers from non-existant rules and charters all day long, it makes no difference.  I've never argued the purpose of the forum, I've always argued the way in which it was created AND the fact that it should not be allowed to exist outside of RTA control.  In the former case, you are following rules that you are making up along the way ...in the latter case, it's just you wanting to be special.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1) Some folks will vote yes simply to have access to it because they believe spoilers will be present, not because they care to see a debate process.<br>
2) Some folks will vote yes simply to vote yes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Just so I'm clear on this, you don't want a vote to be called because you can't control what people might be thinking when they vote?<br>
<br>
This is the most pathetic display of respect for your fellow man I've ever had the misfortune of witnessing first hand.  I don't suppose the fact that your fellow RTA Representatives could actually vote in a fair and impartial manner ever crossed your mind, did it?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>3) Even if the vote is &quot;yes&quot;, all the information that is in the forum will have to be deleted as it was placed there under the pretense that it was of limited access. If it isn't deleted before the forum is made public, then some of the authors may have justification in filing a lawsuit based on their copyrighted posts and distribution rights.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Lol ...you are gonna sue us now?  Copyrighted posts?  Distribution rights?  Are you serious?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4) Even if the vote is &quot;yes&quot;, the current members of the EP forum will simply take their discussions elsewhere and the RTA EP forum will be dead...<br>
<br>
The most that calling a vote will do is cause the forums to move elsewhere.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Aww, I'm sorry ... want me to hold the door open?<br>
<br>
I think it shows a great deal of your true character when you would take your precious little EP community circle jerk forum elsewhere rather than to make yourselves accountable to the community to which you are supposed to belong.<br>
<br>
It's all about being special, though, isn't it?  It's all about being different than everyone else, isn't it? <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->These are stupid ideas and these people should be given a damn good thrashing with a clue stick.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.clanbashemded.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.clanbashemded.org/images/rigsig.gif" style="border:0;height:150;width:300;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=438887" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;">Magelo Profile</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dovelyngoldenheart>Dovelyn Goldenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Less post, m0 play!</span><br>  Posts: 1060<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/4/03 9:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Elemental planes forum</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I think it shows a great deal of your true character when you would take your precious little EP community circle jerk forum elsewhere rather than to make yourselves accountable to the community to which you are supposed to belong.<br>
<br>
It's all about being special, though, isn't it? It's all about being different than everyone else, isn't it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's all about doing it the way it has always been done... in private... while still keeping a record of the discussions so that future elemental guilds can see it instead of going off word of mouth and memory as has been done in the past.  It is an improvement, but you can't (won't) see that. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26803" target="top">Dovelyn Goldenheart</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Archon<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52918" target="top">Fianna Treewind</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Wizard</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=htt